Module org.nasdanika.common
Package org.nasdanika.common

Interface Supplier<T>

Record Components:
C - context type.
T - result type.
All Superinterfaces:
AutoCloseable, Diagnosable, ExecutionParticipant, ExecutionParticipantInfo, Function<ProgressMonitor,T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
ContextifiedExecutionParticipant.ContextifiedSupplier, ElementIdentityMapCompoundSupplier, ExecGenObjectLoaderSupplier, ExecObjectLoaderSupplier, FilterSupplier, ListCompoundSupplier, MapCompoundSupplier, NcoreObjectLoaderSupplier, StringMapCompoundSupplier
public interface Supplier<T> extends ExecutionParticipant, ExecutionParticipantInfo, Function<ProgressMonitor,T>
By convention Supplier does not split the monitor for itself - this is the responsibility of the caller. ProgressMonitor allocation pattern - the caller creates a monitor with work's size and name and passes it to work's execute: ``` try (Supplier supplier = ...; ProgressMonitor workMonitor = monitor.split(supplier.getName(), supplier.getSize(), supplier)) { work.execute(workMonitor); // If success work.commit(); // If something went wrong work.rollback(); } ```
Author:
Pavel Vlasov
